Define core structs: app, group, command, option, arg. The command tree is the central data structure that everything else builds on. Options need: flags list, short aliases, type, boolean/count inference, :multiple, :required, :default, :env, :nargs, :help, :group (for help display). Args need: name, type, :required, :default, :nargs (:rest/+/N), :help. Groups and commands need: name, :aliases, handler, parent ref, children list. App needs: name, version, env-prefix.
** Design
*** File: clime-core.el (replace skeleton structs)

Replace the placeholder `clime-thing` with the real command tree structs.
All structs use `cl-defstruct` with `:constructor` prefix `clime-TYPE--create`
and `:copier nil` (matching the skeleton convention).

*** Structs

**** clime-param (abstract base for option + arg)
Not a real struct — shared slots documented here, duplicated in option/arg.
- name (symbol) — canonical param name, used as plist key in parsed result
- type (symbol or function) — type converter, default 'string
- help (string) — one-line description for --help
- required (boolean)
- default — default value (or a function for lazy defaults)
- nargs — nil (=1), integer N, or :rest

**** clime-option
- name (symbol) — canonical name
- flags (list of strings) — e.g. ("--verbose" "-v")
- type (symbol) — default 'string
- help (string)
- required (boolean)
- default — default value
- nargs — nil means 1 for value options, 0 for boolean/count
- env (string) — env var name override
- count (boolean) — if t, flag is a counter (-vvv → 3)
- multiple (boolean) — if t, repeated flags collect into a list
- group (string) — help display group label
- hidden (boolean) — omit from help

Derived properties (not stored, computed):
- boolean-p: t when count=t or type=boolean or nargs=0
- short-flags: flags matching "^-[^-]$"
- long-flags: flags matching "^--"

**** clime-arg
- name (symbol) — canonical name
- type (symbol) — default 'string
- help (string)
- required (boolean) — default t
- default — default value (may be a function)
- nargs — nil (=1), integer N, or :rest

**** clime-node (abstract base for group + command)
Not a real struct — shared slots:
- name (string) — command/group name as typed by user
- aliases (list of strings)
- help (string) — one-line description
- options (list of clime-option)
- args (list of clime-arg)
- parent — ref to parent node or nil (root)
- hidden (boolean)

**** clime-command (leaf node)
Inherits node slots plus:
- handler (function) — called with a clime-context

**** clime-group (branch node)
Inherits node slots plus:
- children (list of clime-node) — subcommands and subgroups
- invoke (function or nil) — optional handler when group is invoked without subcommand
  (default: print help)

**** clime-app (root, extends group)
Inherits group slots plus:
- version (string)
- env-prefix (string) — for auto-deriving env var names
- json-mode (boolean) — whether --json is a built-in root option

*** Constructors
Public constructors: `clime-make-option`, `clime-make-arg`,
`clime-make-command`, `clime-make-group`, `clime-make-app`.
Each validates required fields and normalizes (e.g. ensure flags
are strings, name is a string).

*** Key design choices
- Flat structs, no inheritance via cl-defstruct :include — keeps it simple.
  clime-command and clime-group share slots by convention, not by struct
  hierarchy. A `clime-node-p` predicate checks both types.
- Parent refs set during tree registration, not at construction time.
- The `args` list is ordered — position matters for parsing.
- `options` list is unordered — lookup is by flag string.
- `children` in group is an alist (name . node) for O(1) lookup + ordering.

*** Accessors / queries
- `clime-node-p` — test if arg is command or group
- `clime-option-boolean-p` — derived predicate
- `clime-node-find-option` — lookup option by flag string in node
- `clime-node-all-ancestor-flags` — collect flags from all ancestors (for collision checks)
- `clime-group-find-child` — lookup child by name or alias
** Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] clime-option struct exists with all slots: name, flags, type, help, required, default, nargs, env, count, multiple, group, hidden
- [ ] clime-arg struct exists with all slots: name, type, help, required, default, nargs
- [ ] clime-command struct exists with: name, aliases, help, options, args, parent, hidden, handler
- [ ] clime-group struct exists with: name, aliases, help, options, args, parent, hidden, children, invoke
- [ ] clime-app struct exists extending group with: version, env-prefix, json-mode
- [ ] Public constructors validate required fields (name for all, flags for option, handler for command)
- [ ] clime-option-boolean-p returns t for count=t, type=boolean, nargs=0
- [ ] clime-node-p returns t for both command and group structs
- [ ] clime-node-find-option looks up an option by any of its flag strings
- [ ] clime-group-find-child looks up child by name or alias
- [ ] children stored as alist for O(1) lookup
- [ ] args list is ordered (position-sensitive)
- [ ] ERT tests cover all constructors, predicates, and lookups
- [ ] Placeholder clime-thing removed
** Plan
1. Replace clime-core.el contents:
   - Remove placeholder clime-thing struct and functions
   - Add cl-defstruct for clime-option (all slots, :constructor clime-option--create)
   - Add cl-defstruct for clime-arg (:constructor clime-arg--create)
   - Add cl-defstruct for clime-command (:constructor clime-command--create)
   - Add cl-defstruct for clime-group (:constructor clime-group--create)
   - Add cl-defstruct for clime-app (:include clime-group, :constructor clime-app--create)
     App extends group via :include since it truly is a group (has children, options, etc.)

2. Add public constructors with validation:
   - clime-make-option — requires :name and non-empty :flags, defaults type to 'string
   - clime-make-arg — requires :name, defaults type to 'string and required to t
   - clime-make-command — requires :name and :handler
   - clime-make-group — requires :name
   - clime-make-app — requires :name, defaults version to nil

3. Add predicates and queries:
   - clime-option-boolean-p — check count, type=boolean, nargs=0
   - clime-node-p — check command-p or group-p (app-p covered by group include)
   - clime-node-find-option — iterate node options, match flag in flags list
   - clime-group-find-child — check alist by name, then scan aliases
   - clime-node-all-ancestor-flags — walk parent chain collecting flags

4. Run tests, fix any issues.



